[thinking] **Exploring method reachability**
[thinking] 
[thinking] I’m thinking about using a public bridge with JUnit's @MethodSource, but I wonder if the dynamic-access report will only recognize invokestatic callers. To make a method reachable in a native image, I might need reflection metadata, but I'm not modifying it. However, if I use Java reflection in test code to call Method.invoke on class$, the native image analysis could include that method body if it’s reflectively registered. I’m curious if MethodHandles.privateLookupIn would be visible during analysis, but apparently it isn't.
[thinking] 
[thinking] **Inspecting metadata and reachability**
[thinking] 
[thinking] I'm pondering how reachability might be tied to existing metadata generated from the agent. I wonder if this metadata reflects methods invoked reflectively but not during native compilation. It’s interesting that the dynamic-access report is based on static analysis, which includes reflection call sites rather than runtime data. I think it might be useful to inspect DynamicAccessUtils for deeper insights into this whole concept!
