[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Exploring method reachability**\n\nI’m thinking about using a public bridge with JUnit's @MethodSource, but I wonder if the dynamic-access report will only recognize invokestatic callers. To make a method reachable in a native image, I might need reflection metadata, but I'm not modifying it. However, if I use Java reflection in test code to call Method.invoke on class$, the native image analysis could include that method body if it’s reflectively registered. I’m curious if MethodHandles.privateLookupIn would be visible during analysis, but apparently it isn't.\n\n**Inspecting metadata and reachability**\n\nI'm pondering how reachability might be tied to existing metadata generated from the agent. I wonder if this metadata reflects methods invoked reflectively but not during native compilation. It’s interesting that the dynamic-access report is based on static analysis, which includes reflection call sites rather than runtime data. I think it might be useful to inspect DynamicAccessUtils for deeper insights into this whole concept!", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0d54a6668778010b016a009839ce208196bf06b761a8da1452\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqAJhEIIorGUC1OuvKpEfuuWDwT1qCe441Xwg9qCVrGq5hbjWdHc57-iS6CqDe_i26mAH8fq1-LiG0a-yqJzoAPIsljGsrfxdk81hSXPjiG5ETBFNROMI2tOVaWJAR8MmYdOuDvVY9pfFAB_Vi8jl49c0bfOQ1NIMKH6IUIRosjNXb5oc5GO2xqWYEb5XoCmnloJKR9Gd8vcYV6C14_18h3nrVz_3EcHvTqujGMfjbjk-w87E-BLsmqoxY1qbNoPxKjkRbopk_DJ8i1vLjg0d-zdKLLDq7gd7C5bcb5ERkJi7zCM1vrbU-Mrp8Knb-gBnZm7K3A0yVmMzfwMAivsRHnOQe00VCkWQeTIWvf7cnJzQmV2SlkyuBLiXYwn7rRrzDJBYNhIyQz_SIup_W55HiLyDhc7sYq5xfMK4duj1mNhAgwjc1eqMffo2xQ7CkPnq5cFRnrBVMDbt9bhWJz3EoAQgR9qWM8CEW1yjetegeUNeUGlGuOio5HMRx7zsHwoRdsNBCLzh321G4eHtyg0rEhLWuJa88_dqEuJ55kuLY_SzlpeTxDpmHIr_PdYr1-1vjC46TiW0t_5qzA3vj1GrXF2v7v81cClduKkqdvAcyk0-6me0RrZFGZ9KEn4kuq0CLgG_tWIJ6ViKPGmqFMGEYzS_qlUbfrpVWYKJdpAcdv9yYcQ4ttQGJA7VgL3